# Markdown Style Guide - Quick Reference

**When writing or editing markdown files, follow `docs/guides/MARKDOWN_LINTING_GUIDE.md`**

## üö® MANDATORY Workflow Before Committing Markdown

1. **Run `make fix-md`** - Auto-fixes common issues (tables, trailing spaces, blank lines)
2. **Self-check** - Scan for these issues:
   - [ ] Only one H1 (`#`) in the document
   - [ ] Blank line after all headings
   - [ ] No trailing spaces
   - [ ] Lists have blank lines before and after
   - [ ] Code fences have language specifiers (` ```python `, ` ```bash `, etc.)
   - [ ] Tables use consistent spacing around pipes
   - [ ] No multiple consecutive blank lines
3. **Run `make lint-markdown`** - Verify no linting errors
4. **Run `make docs`** - Validate docs build (catches broken links, missing nav entries)

## Common Issues & Fixes

### Tables (MD060)
```markdown
‚úÖ Good:
| Header | Column2 |
| ------ | ------- |
| Value1 | Value2  |

‚ùå Bad (no spaces around pipes):
|Header|Column2|
|------|-------|
|Value1|Value2|
```

### Lists (MD032)
```markdown
‚úÖ Good:
Paragraph text.

- List item 1
- List item 2

Another paragraph.

‚ùå Bad (no blank lines):
Paragraph text.
- List item 1
- List item 2
Another paragraph.
```

### Code Blocks (MD040)
```markdown
‚úÖ Good - always specify language:
```python
def example():
    pass
```

‚ùå Bad - no language:
```
def example():
    pass
```
```

### Blank Lines After Headings
```markdown
‚úÖ Good:
## Heading

Paragraph text.

‚ùå Bad:
## Heading
Paragraph text.
```

## Auto-Fix Command

```bash
# Fix all markdown files
make fix-md

# Or directly
python scripts/fix_markdown.py

# Fix specific files
python scripts/fix_markdown.py docs/TESTING_STRATEGY.md

# Dry run (preview fixes)
python scripts/fix_markdown.py --dry-run
```

## What `fix_markdown.py` Fixes

- ‚úÖ Table separator formatting (MD060)
- ‚úÖ Trailing spaces (MD009)
- ‚úÖ Blank lines around lists (MD032)
- ‚úÖ Code block language specifiers (MD040) - when detectable
- ‚úÖ Blank lines around code fences (MD031)
- ‚úÖ Multiple blank lines (MD012)

## When to Run

- **Before committing** any markdown files
- **After bulk edits** to documentation
- **When CI fails** on markdown linting

